.TH "BSON_WRITER_NEW" "3" "2014-08-19" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_writer_new()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
bson_writer_t *
bson_writer_new (uint8_t         **buf,
                 size_t           *buflen,
                 size_t            offset,
                 bson_realloc_func realloc_func,
                 void             *realloc_func_ctx);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B .B buf
A uint8_t.
.LP
.TP
.B .B buflen
A size_t.
.LP
.TP
.B .B offset
A size_t.
.LP
.TP
.B .B realloc_func
A bson_realloc_func.
.LP
.TP
.B .B realloc_func_ctx
A bson_realloc_func.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Creates a new instance of
.BR bson_writer_t
using the
.B buffer
,
.B length
,
.B offset
, and _realloc()_ function supplied.

The caller is expected to clean up the structure when finished using
.BR bson_writer_destroy(3)
\&.

.SH "RETURNS"

A newly allocated bson_writer_t.


